# Disease.create!(name:"Homonymous Hemianopsia", symptoms:"Bumping into or failing to notice things on the side of the hemianopsia. This can make such everyday tasks as crossing the street or driving a car unsafe. Missing parts of words or parts of an eye chart on the side of the hemianopsia when reading. Not noticing objects on a desk or table, or even food on a plate to the side of the hemianopsia. Frustration with reading because it is difficult for the eyes to pick up the beginning of the next line. Tendency to turn the head or body away from the side of the hemianopsia. Drifting in a direction away from the hemianopsia when walking. Visual hallucinations that appear in the form of lights, shapes, or geometric figures or as the image of a recognizable object. Sometimes a movement noted on the normal side of vision is believed to be also seen at the same time on the side of the visual loss.", description:"Hemianopsia or hemianopia is a visual field loss on the left or right side of the vertical midline.Homonymous hemianopsia occurs because the right half of the brain has visual pathways for the left hemifield of both eyes, and the left half of the brain has visual pathways for the right hemifield of both eyes. When one of these pathways is damaged, the corresponding visual field is lost.")

